text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia megacephala is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Mid West regions of Western Australia.The erect, spindly and spinose shrub typically grows to a height of 0.9 to 2 metres (3 to 7 ft). It blooms from July to September and produces yellow flowers.
